definition: to hit/to strike/to tap/to rap/to knock/to rip sb off/to overcharge
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]

sentences.english: So that part is pretty clear, so hit Y for yes.
sentences.chinese: 这大家都懂的吧，所以敲入Y，也就是保存。

sentences.english: She placed the nail and hammered it into the thick log wall.
sentences.chinese: 她立好钉子，用锤子将它敲入厚实的木墙。

sentences.english: You do not want the repo man knockin at your door.
sentences.chinese: 你不想在你的门回购男子敲入。
